abstract: >-
  A production Claude Code configuration that enforces an anti-hallucination
  methodology through deterministic Python hooks, evidence policy rules,
  and specialized agents. Detects and blocks "Validation Theater" —
  the pattern where AI agents validate claims using synthetic data and
  report false success. Includes 89 hooks across 25 event types, 13 agents
  + 3 teams, 125 skills, 14 rule files, with 2237 tests at 80% coverage
  and CI gates on Linux + Windows. Designed for AI engineers working with
  sensitive data (PII, finance, healthcare) where Evidence Policy must be
  enforced as a hard rule rather than as instruction text.
